subSubSection.paragraph:
Diagnosis.
Characters, in combination, which serve to distinguish 

Chasmodes longimaxilla

: dentary teeth sharply pointed and recurved; mandibular pores 4–6 (usually 4; 
Table 2
); ventral lip flaps not prominent; upper jaw length 40.0–60.6% of head length; gill rakers 9–12 (usually 11).
